    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "TWA\nTRAN'S WÖRLD",
      "TWA-TRANS WORLD AIRLINES\nBoeing 747SP-31\nTWA purchased three 747SPs, ultra long-range version of\nthe 747, for delivery in early 1980. These\n\"special perfor-\nmance\" aircraft are ideally suited for longer intercontinental\nflights, and have a range of nearly 6,900 statute miles.\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nB-037\n83163-D\npost card\nPhoto courtesv Trans World Airlines\nN58201 c/n 21961\n2002.113.492"
    ],
